  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Quotation marks run through fiction, interviews, and half the messages you send. They are worth getting right."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Open a quote and your hands should already know to close it. Let that pairing become reflex, not a decision."
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "target": "\"What time is the meeting?\" Sarah asked. \"At three,\" David replied, \"in the main conference room.\" She",
      "finger": "purple",
      "hint": "Quotes + dialogue rhythm"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "The little tags, he said and she asked, are the quiet hinges of a scene. Type them without a pause and the conversation keeps its pace."
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "target": "nodded. \"Should I bring the report?\" \"Yes,\" he said, \"and the projections too. They'll want to see both.\"",
