  "character_tips": {
    "anna": "Dialogue is the trickiest punctuation there is. Master it and the rest of writing feels easy. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "maxim": "A good deal of business writing is one person quoting another. Drill these marks until they are automatic. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "knopych": "Two voices, back and forth. The marks keep them apart, so set them down cleanly and stay in step. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "klavochka": "A conversation set on the page. Get the quotes right and the reader hears every word. - Eleanor Hayes, editor"
